                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/377: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-09T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 9, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>873. My 854, October 3, 8 p.m. Following from American Consul at Harbin: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 8, 4 p.m. Reliably informed Soviet regulars or partisans
                            recently killed unarmed male inhabitants White Cossack villages, Three
                            Rivers district, Heilungkiang Province, reasons unknown, possibly
                            provocation to cause White indignation against the Reds.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
